bj.</pos> </gramGrp> <ref cRef="Num." loc="22,13">Num. 22,13</ref>; <ref cRef="Kuf." loc="29">Kuf. 29</ref>; <ref cRef="Kuf." loc="41">Kuf. 41</ref>; vel <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወ፡</foreign> <lbl expand="cum">c.</lbl> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Subjunctivus">Subj.</pos> </gramGrp> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኅድገኒ፡ ወኣጥፍኦሙ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Deut." loc="9,14">Deut. 9,14</ref>.</sense> </sense> <sense n="B" xml:id="DB"> intransitive: <sense n="1" xml:id="DB1"> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> remittere </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> cessare </quote></cit> (<cit type="translation" xml:lang="de"><quote> nachlassen </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="de"><quote> ablassen </quote></cit>): <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኀደገ፡ እሳት፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Num." loc="11,2">Num. 11,2</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ብድብድ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Num." loc="17,13">Num. 17,13</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">መቅሠፍት፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Num." loc="25,8">Num. 25,8</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሀቦ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Ex." loc="16,13">Ex. 16,13</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ነፋስ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Matth. " loc="14,32">Matth.  14,32</ref>; <ref cRef="Marc." loc="6,51">Marc. 6,51</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለምጽ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Lev." loc="13,5">Lev. 13,5</ref>; <ref cRef="Lev." loc="13,51">Lev. 13,51</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">የኀድግ፡ እዴሁ፡ እምላዕሌክሙ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="1 Reg. " loc="6,3">1 Reg.  6,3</ref>.</sense> <sense n="2" xml:id="DB2"> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> deficere </quote></cit>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ትጸውም፡ ወትጼሊ፡ እስከ፡ ኀደገ፡ ሥጋሃ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Sx. Mag." loc="20.">Sx. Mag. 20.</ref> </sense> <sense n="3" xml:id="DB3"> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> cedere </quote></cit> alicui in re, eo <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> inferiorem esse </quote></cit>, <lbl expand="cum">c.</lbl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">እምነ፡</foreign> comparativo: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘይባርክ፡ ዐርኮ፡ በጽባሕ፡ በዐቢይ፡ ቃል፡ እምዘይረግም፡ አልቦ፡ ዘኀደገ፡</foreign> (<foreign xml:lang="grc">οὐδὲν διαφέρει</foreign>) <ref cRef="Prov. " loc="27,14">Prov.  27,14</ref>.</sense> </sense> </sense>
               
            <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> ḫadaga </quote></cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢይትኅደግ፡ እንበለ፡</foreign> + Subjunctive <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> surely, certainly </quote></cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢይትኀድግ፡ እንበለ፡ ይፍታህ፡ ለነ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ እምዝንቱ፡ ሞኰንን፡ ዓመፃ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote> “Il ne se peut que le Seigneur ne nous rende pas justice contre cet officier pervers!” </quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengel"/><citedRange unit="page"> 21 l. 34–35 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengelV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 25 l. 38–39 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> <sense n="E" xml:id="TE"> This same construction occurs in Amharic <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስ-</foreign> + NEG Imperfect <foreign xml:lang="gez">አይቀርም</foreign> <lbl expand="literally">lit.</lbl> ‘it will not remain without Verb’. It needs to be researched whether Amharic inherited this construction or whether the Gǝʿǝz construction is a calque from Amharic. Note that in the above example the construction occurs in direct speech. </sense> </sense>
